&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Benefits:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Can't submit while already submitting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Validation happens in its own state&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Error and success are mutually exclusive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Clear paths for retry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you're using XState, this maps directly. If you prefer a lighter approach, even a plain TypeScript discriminated union gets you most of the way:&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

